-- Russian Economy Grew 2.4% in June, Most in 19 Months, VTB Indicator Shows
-- Paul Abelsky
-- 2010-07-06T05:27:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/russian-economy-grew-2-4-in-june-most-in-19-months-vtb-indicator-shows.html

          
          
             Russia’s economy expanded an annual
2.4 percent last month, the fastest pace since November 2008,
VTB Capital said.  
 The data “points to a continued recovery across the
Russian manufaturing and service sectors,” VTB Capital said in
its monthly GDP Indicator report.  
